==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Triforium
<hw>Tri*fo"ri*um</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[LL., fr. L.
<ets>tri-</ets> (see <er>Tri-</er>) + <ets>foris</ets>, pl.
<ets>fores</ets>, a door.]</ety> <fld>(Arch.)</fld> <def>The gallery or
open space between the vaulting and the roof of the aisles of a church,
often forming a rich arcade in the interior of the church, above the
nave arches and below the clearstory windows.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Triform</ent>⟦br⟧
